external_knowledge:
- 'Champions of the season' refers to teams with the highest win rate in the specified season;
- 'Win rate' is calculated as the total number of wins divided by the total number of matches played;
- 'Epic saga of this particular season' refers to the specific season name provided in the query.

- "Shining star" refers to the player who has been awarded the Man of the Match the most times;
- "Led their team to victory" means the player's team won the match;
- "Toss winner decided to bat" indicates the team that won the toss chose to bat first;
- "Normal win" refers to a win that did not involve a super over.

- 'Normal outcome' refers to matches that concluded without issues or abandonment;
- 'Match type 1' is likely to refer to international matches;
- The term "Team" in a team name is a specific substring used for filtering.

- "better overall performance" refers to teams with a higher number of wins over all matches;
- "recently experienced a decline" refers to teams that have fewer wins in their most recent five matches compared to their overall performance;
- "more than two recent losses" refers to teams that have lost more than two of their most recent five matches.

- In cricket, winning the toss can sometimes give a team a strategic advantage;
- The team that wins the toss decides whether to bat first or second;
- The query focuses on teams that have capitalized on this advantage by winning the match after winning the toss.
